DON'T GET ANY BLOOD
ON YOUR GOOD SHOES.

00:55.522 --> 00:56.957
WHO'S THE GIRL?

00:59.860 --> 01:04.304
DO YOU WANT HER
TO LIVE?

01:04.304 --> 01:05.706
PLEASE.

01:08.542 --> 01:09.976
LET HER LIVE.

01:13.279 --> 01:15.716
[ CLATTERING ]

01:15.716 --> 01:19.152
NOW, THIS IS A MESS.

01:19.152 --> 01:21.287
BOYS DID WHAT THEY HAD
TO DO, ALL RIGHT?

01:21.287 --> 01:24.390
GOOD THING
I OWN THE POLICE.

01:24.390 --> 01:26.359
I'M SORRY, GRANDMA.

01:26.359 --> 01:28.094
DON'T BE SORRY.

01:28.094 --> 01:29.763
IS THIS HIM?

01:29.763 --> 01:32.165
IT WAS.

01:32.165 --> 01:34.134
OKAY.

01:34.134 --> 01:36.069
DONE.

01:36.069 --> 01:38.905
LOOK AT MY RESTAURANT.

01:38.905 --> 01:41.041
YEAH. IT'S A MESS.

01:43.610 --> 01:45.145
I'M SORRY, ALL RIGHT?

01:45.145 --> 01:47.147
DON'T BE SORRY.

01:47.147 --> 01:49.449
THANK YOU.

01:49.449 --> 01:50.450
I MEAN,
I DIDN'T REALLY DO TOO MUCH.

01:50.450 --> 01:54.555
IT WAS MOSTLY...
THANK CANDACE.

01:54.555 --> 01:57.323
HOW DO YOU KNOW HER?

01:57.323 --> 02:00.026
SHE'S BEEN HERE BEFORE.

02:00.026 --> 02:01.134
WHAT?

02:03.436 --> 02:05.138
I OWE HER.

02:08.241 --> 02:09.976
GOOD WORK, TONY.

02:09.976 --> 02:11.144
YOU'RE WELCOME.

02:14.080 --> 02:15.381
GRANDMA.

02:19.853 --> 02:21.121
SEE YOU SOON.

02:25.826 --> 02:27.894
WHO'S GONNA CLEAN
THIS...UP?

